item.title: RuneScape Pre-194
item.dc:creator: @Docent Limits
item.description:
@Docent wrote:

[quote=“Newty, post:12, topic:542170”][quote author=Docent link=topic=661046.msg4419129#msg4419129 date=1397527366]

runecrafting was released in march 2004.

rs2 beta was released in december of 2003.

that’s a 4 month difference.

either 194 had runecrafting and there are prior revisions which we have no recollection of (as seen above)
or 194 didn’t have runecrafting and everyone is just dumb.

194 sure did have, just check the server/client Docent released using a real 194 deob

There is no 194 cache. The client is a 194 but it is hacked to load like a 317 or 30* cache. Also, just because his server has runecrafting doesn’t mean 194 had runecrafting. My servers in 2007 had summoning and that was long before runescape actually had it.

I’m not talking about project Osiris.

just check this one: https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,659138.0.html

“I released this because I really hope someone can load 289 map data onto it (objects) and also get far.”

He ISN’T loading the 194 cache. From the looks of it he wants to load a 289 which might be the oldest cache that our scene has available.

No this is a 194 cache, it has the original 194 landscape files but is missing mapdata which to my understanding is all the buildings and objects that are located on the ground. That is the only thing that is missing from the package and the closest thing we have is 289 objects

[/quote]

So is it a corrupted 194 cache? I’d prefer if Taharok saw this and answered it[/quote]

Same

Read full topic
